13.2 Social-Media-Plug-ins
We have embedded functions of the respective social networks on our website (so-called plug-ins). If you use these functions to share or comment on the linked content, a direct connection will be established to the servers of the respective social networks. We embedded the functions of the social networks so that the networks only receive the information accessed on our website once you actually interact with the respective social plug-in and not when you first access our page. If you logged into the respective social network with your user name and password while interacting with the respective social plug-ins, information regarding your visit to our page is transmitted to the plug-in and the respective provider can allocate this information to your user account. If you interact with the social plug-in, i.e. you use the Facebook “Like” or Twitter “Tweet This” function for example, the contents of our pages will then be linked and shared with your Facebook or Twitter profile. If you are not a member of the respective social networks or logged out from the provider prior to visiting our website, it is still possible for your IP address to be transmitted and saved if you interact with the respective social plug-ins. Please note that the content and scope of the data that is directly collected and transmitted by the social networks via the social plug-ins as well as the storage duration of up to 250 days and the intended purpose is explicitly determined by the respective providers. We have no influence on this transmission of information. Please obtain further information from the data protection notices of the provider linked above. The legal basis of the inclusion of social plug-ins is Article 6 para. 1, clause 1 f) of the GDPR based on our legitimate interest in the provision of the aforementioned social network functions.
13.3 LinkedIn Analytics and LinkedIn Ads
